SIMPLE: forehead
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forehead
<hw>Fore"head</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
front of that part of the head which incloses the brain; that part of
the face above the eyes; the brow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The aspect or countenance; assurance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To look with <qex>forehead</qex> bold and big enough⟦br⟧
Upon the power and puissance of the king.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The front or fore part of anything.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Flames in the <qex>forehead</qex> of the morning sky.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So rich advantage of a promised glory⟦br⟧
As smiles upon the <qex>forehead</qex> of this action.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forehear</ent>⟦br⟧
